President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of South Dakota due to severe storms, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred between June 13-20, 2014. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state, local, and tribal recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repairing or replacing damaged facilities, and implementing hazard mitigation measures. Gary R. Stanley has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made if requested by the state and deemed necessary based on damage assessments.